ce:section.ce:para:
To gain a better insight into the influence of various parameters on the solvatochromic behaviour of C-dot, we take a closer look at the wavelength-dependency plots of C-dot dispersed in water, dioxane and 1-propanol; for water (Fig. 4a) as solvent (
α = 1.17
), the emission wavelengths we detected, span a broader range compared to 1-propanol (
α = 0.76
) and aprotic solvent such as dioxane (
α = 0.0
) (Fig. 4b and ESI Fig. S3), and this reinforces the hypothesis that the slightest interaction through hydrogen bonding occurred when C-dots were transferred to less hydrophilic alcohol and aprotic solvents.
